rebirth WP5 — ablation intervention at build_cvec (DECISIONS.md D-012 / D-016)

Adds a sibling adapter `llama_adapter_intervene` next to the native control
vector, applied inside `llm_graph_context::build_cvec` AFTER the control vector,
so it forces chosen residual neurons to a fixed value: per genuinely-ablated
layer it emits `cur * mask + add` (mask[k]=0, add[k]=value pins neuron k). This
is the `llm_ablate()` mechanism (D-012 pre-authorized; semantics D-016).

Provenance record (DECISIONS.md D-015): this diff is the human-readable delta of
the committed, patched `src/llama.cpp/` tree against upstream b9726. `build.rs`
compiles the committed tree as-is (no build-time patching). `vendor-bump`
re-applies this diff to a fresh upstream checkout; the CI patch-coherence check
reverse-applies it and asserts the pre-patch pruned-tree SHA256.

Paths are relative to rebirth/src/llama.cpp/ (git diff --relative), so:
  git apply       patches/0001-rebirth-wp5-ablation-intervene.diff   # apply
  git apply -R    patches/0001-rebirth-wp5-ablation-intervene.diff   # revert
both run from rebirth/src/llama.cpp/.

Hunks (each also carries an inline `rebirth WP5` code comment):
  include/llama.h          public C API `rebirth_set_intervene` (project-prefixed)
  src/llama-adapter.h      struct llama_adapter_intervene + _ptr alias
  src/llama-adapter.cpp    mask_for / apply_to (cur*mask+add) / apply (full
                           coverage from layer 0; tensors only for non-identity,
                           i.e. genuinely-ablated, layers)
  src/llama-context.h      set_intervene decl + llama_adapter_intervene_ptr member
  src/llama-context.cpp    ctor init; set_intervene impl; graph_params wiring;
                           public rebirth_set_intervene C entry
  src/llama-graph.h        intervene ptr in llm_graph_params and llm_graph_context;
                           intervene == other.intervene in allow_reuse (graph reuse)
  src/llama-graph.cpp      intervene(params.intervene) init; build_cvec applies
                           intervene->apply_to after cvec->apply_to (no-op, no
                           graph node, when no ablation is registered)

